<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>A guild like HnE will have mandatory raiding requirements and if you just never feel like raiding, you won't stay part of the guild, because you don't contribute. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Wellll with DKP you can leave them in, if they're good people who want to raid but cannot, they just almost never get loot.  If you never &quot;feel like raiding&quot; rather than you just cannot because of RL, that's a little different.<br>
<br>
You can be a social guild that has a large portion which raids regularly, just that eventually those people will get sick of the players who log on but don't feel like raiding, and leave to join the guilds full of people who &quot;choose to&quot; raid all the time.  I don't know if you'd call that stable, but to me that goes against what the original poster meant to achieve.  All it takes is a few of those times where you have like 80 people on, 40 of those being hardcore players who want to do a raid that takes your guild 60-70, and not have enough of the casual people want to go (yet be online), and the hardcore people take off.<br>
