<br>
With a bidding system, people never feel like they over-paid - they were the ones who bid. Also, in some sense it is need before greed. If I have a (made up numbers for simplification) 10 AC bp and someone else has a 30 AC bp and a 50 AC bp drops, it means mroe to me than it does to the other person. So I may bid more points than the other person, because I want it more. But if this second person also wants it badly, and they bid the same price and have more DKP, then it appropriately (in my opinion) awards the item to the second player. My fault for not participating.<br>
<br>
