--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> ToN hasn't really been what I'd call &quot;stable&quot;, though. That's more or less my point.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
We've actually been alot more stable than any guild I can think of since the Laurri coup, with the exception--perhaps--of your own.<br>
<br>
I do not however think we can continue to describe outselves as &quot;casual&quot;--we are friendly, certainly. But many people work way too hard for us for that to be casual.<br>
<br>
I am not one of them, but I do recognize that without them I'd be lfg in sebilis. Which would be lonely since there is no one there.<br>
<br>
A few points in general:<br>
<br>
1.) Loot to the casual player. In my experience, which is pretty much casual (more than it should be lately:P), there's plenty of loot to go around. Perfectly nice things go up for grabs often enough that it isn't hard to equip decently raiding like twice a week. (Although the guilt factor of not doing more is something to consider.) People who whine about that...would be whining about something else if not that, ignore them.<br>
<br>
Sure, you're not going to see the best drops first--but if you are patient, you will see them. <br>
<br>
2.) Sharing the load. No one can do everything all the time or forever. Everyone needs to take time off at some point. Your guild must have the flexibility to realize that, and the ability to share responsibilies so that no one goes insane.<br>
<br>
3.) Trust. Well, obviously...<br>
<br>
4.) Realistic expectations. Everyone wants to conquer the world, someday--but you can't start doing Talendor and expect to be in Plane of Time in six months. Be proud of what you can accomplish and the rest will follow...and it is pretty neat when it does. I always get misty-eyed remembering our first Aary kill... <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~luckythedog/EQ/Vainnesig2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=418857">Vainne Niteblind, Saryrn</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nandarie>Nandarie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 3244<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(7/22/03 4:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5270.topic&index=37>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.mwscomp.com/movies/grail/jpgs/timencha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;We've actually been alot more stable than any guild I can think of since the Laurri coup, with the exception--perhaps--of your own.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
